   139→## Versions
   141→A "version" is described by the `v2.0.0` specification found at
   142→<https://semver.org/>.
   143→
   144→A leading `"="` or `"v"` character is stripped off and ignored.
   145→Support for stripping a leading "v" is kept for compatibility with `v1.0.0` of the SemVer
   146→specification but should not be used anymore.
   147→
   148→## Ranges
   150→A `version range` is a set of `comparators` that specify versions
   151→that satisfy the range.
   152→
   153→A `comparator` is composed of an `operator` and a `version`.  The set
   154→of primitive `operators` is:
   155→
   156→* `<` Less than
   157→* `<=` Less than or equal to
   158→* `>` Greater than
   159→* `>=` Greater than or equal to
   160→* `=` Equal.  If no operator is specified, then equality is assumed,
   161→  so this operator is optional but MAY be included.
   162→
   163→For example, the comparator `>=1.2.7` would match the versions
      →…
