   408→## Functions
   410→All methods and classes take a final `options` object argument.  All
   411→options in this object are `false` by default.  The options supported
   412→are:
   413→
   414→- `loose`: Be more forgiving about not-quite-valid semver strings.
   415→  (Any resulting output will always be 100% strict compliant, of
   416→  course.)  For backwards compatibility reasons, if the `options`
   417→  argument is a boolean value instead of an object, it is interpreted
   418→  to be the `loose` param.
   419→- `includePrerelease`: Set to suppress the [default
   420→  behavior](https://github.com/npm/node-semver#prerelease-tags) of
   421→  excluding prerelease tagged versions from ranges unless they are
   422→  explicitly opted into.
   423→
